Label: Description
Value: Ukraine  administrative level 0-4 boundaries.  See caveats. The administrative level 0 and 1 layers are suitable for database or GIS linkage to the Ukraine - Subnational Population Statistics tables. Vetting and live service provision by Information Technology Outreach Services (ITOS) with funding from USAID. An edge-matched version of this COD-AB is available as Ukraine - Subnational Edge-matched Administrative Boundaries. Unfamiliar users may wish to be informed that administrative level 1 feature [UA80] is Kyiv city.  Feature [UA32] is Kyivska ('Kyiv') oblast.

Label: License
Value: Creative Commons Attribution for Intergovernmental Organisations

Label: Define Methodology
Value: Sourced from Ukraine Kartografia.  P-coding by OCHA and ITOS.

Label: Caveats/Comments
Value: “The Ukrainian government has not fully implemented its new administrative structure reforms in the Autonomous Republic of Crimea [UA01] and Sevastopol [UA85]. Consequently, 31 ADM4 features within the Sevastopol ADM3 polygon retain P-codes that do not correctly conform to [UA8500000]. This will be rectified in a COD-AB update once the government has regained control to the Crimean Peninsula."

Value: This map service contains OCHA Common Operational Datasets for Ukraine: Administrative Boundaries.
